Steel Strips in Talks to Sell 2-3% Stake For Funds, WSJ Says

-- B y   C h r i s   P e t e r s o n
-- 
2011-04-08T05:44:40Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-08/steel-strips-in-talks-to-sell-2-3-stake-for-funds-wsj-says.html
Steel Strips Wheels Ltd. (SSW) , an Indian
auto wheel manufacturer, is in talks with an unidentified
company to sell a stake of between 2 and 3 percent in order to
raise funds for expansion, the Wall Street Journal reported,
citing an interview with Managing Director Dheeraj Garg.  Some of the money raised would be used to build a new
factory, and Steel Strips is looking for above 595 rupees per
share, the newspaper said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Chris Peterson  at 
 cpeterson@bloomberg.net  